00:02:32.130 --> 00:02:33.130
Once Upon A Time In Hollywood Ending
________________

00:02:33.130 --> 00:02:36.560
During the bender, Rick who is sick and tired
of all the hippies goes face to face with

00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:40.340
the killers who have parked up outside the
houses and he warns orders them to leave,

00:02:40.340 --> 00:02:41.340
which they do.

00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:43.810
That doesn’t mean it’s over though and
the group of murderers come up with a new

00:02:43.810 --> 00:02:46.470
plan on Manson’s orders to kill Rick instead.

00:02:46.470 --> 00:02:50.519
To them, it doesn’t really matter who the
target is as long as their message is spread

00:02:50.519 --> 00:02:52.090
so they head back to his house.

00:02:52.090 --> 00:02:56.109
The killers return to the house but what we
get instead of some brutal murders is some

00:02:56.109 --> 00:03:01.341
over the top, highly graphic violence that
has its tongue placed firmly in its cheek.

00:03:01.341 --> 00:03:06.640
It’s all-out war with Rick his wife, Cliff
and the dog all getting into it with the acolytes.

00:03:06.640 --> 00:03:11.450
Eventually, they manage to kill them and overcome
the threat and Tate who lives just next door

00:03:11.450 --> 00:03:14.550
overhears the ruckus and goes out to find
out what happened.

00:03:14.550 --> 00:03:19.310
Rick knows that she’s married to Roman Polanski
but till now he hasn’t really had the opportunity

00:03:19.310 --> 00:03:24.400
to speak to her, however, this is the perfect
introduction to finally get talking to her

00:03:24.400 --> 00:03:26.250
and to get his career back on track.

00:03:26.250 --> 00:03:30.890
The film ends with the two talking like old
friends and we get a happy ending that basically

00:03:30.890 --> 00:03:34.470
rewrites history and makes Rick the hero of
his own movie.

00:03:34.470 --> 00:03:39.010
It’s an awesome ending that in true Tarantino
Fashion lets us look back on the past with

00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:43.030
wishful thinking and makes us wonder what
we could have got had the events played out

00:03:43.030 --> 00:03:44.030
differently.

00:03:44.030 --> 00:03:45.030
Once Upon A Time In Hollywood Fact VS Fiction
________________

00:03:45.030 --> 00:03:47.889
On the whole, the movie actually does stick
to the facts in terms of the main players

00:03:47.889 --> 00:03:53.630
with all of the killers including Tex Watson,
Susan Atkins, Linda Kasabian and Katie all

00:03:53.630 --> 00:03:55.389
having real-life counterparts.

00:03:55.389 --> 00:03:58.760
On the night that they were going to commit
the murders though there was no Rick Dalton

00:03:58.760 --> 00:04:02.019
and thus the group was able to carry out their
brutal killings.

00:04:02.019 --> 00:04:06.250
Though Polanski was a target at the time he
was actually away during the murders and the

00:04:06.250 --> 00:04:09.979
group killed Tate who was 8 months pregnant
and all of her party guests.

00:04:09.979 --> 00:04:14.160
The killings were very brutal and I definitely
recommend that you watch one of the many youtube

00:04:14.160 --> 00:04:16.870
documentaries on the matter if this movie
has piqued your interest.

00:04:16.870 --> 00:04:17.870
When exiting the house they wrote ‘pig’
on the front door in Tate’s blood and it

00:04:17.870 --> 00:04:18.870
really was a horrifying crime.

00:04:18.870 --> 00:04:19.870
Once Upon A Time In Hollywood Ending Explained
________________

00:04:19.870 --> 00:04:23.200
But what does it all mean, well to me the
entire film is a quest for fame and how in

00:04:23.200 --> 00:04:26.550
order to get it and hold onto it we have to
do terrible things.

00:04:26.550 --> 00:04:30.909
Dalton, Booth and even the Mansons are all
focused solely on gaining recognition and

00:04:30.909 --> 00:04:35.270
trying to keep a hold of it as tightly as
possible and to me this symbolises just how

00:04:35.270 --> 00:04:38.560
Hollywood subverts the innocent in exchange
for status.

00:04:38.560 --> 00:04:42.849
The movie business as a whole is all about
the flavor of the month and in the film, even

00:04:42.849 --> 00:04:46.830
though Tate is currently popular, we get the
feeling that deep down she knows that she

00:04:46.830 --> 00:04:47.980
won’t be forever.

00:04:47.980 --> 00:04:53.160
Overall to me, the film is a comment on how
Hollywood romanticizes these aspects and paints

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:58.111
it all out as one big happy ending even though
we know as an audience that this isn’t the

00:04:58.111 --> 00:04:59.300
case.

00:04:59.300 --> 00:05:03.729
Just as Tarantino changed history, Hollywood
does too and the piece should be viewed as

00:05:03.729 --> 00:05:08.849
a parody of how the movie business as a whole
is unwilling to show it’s dark underside

00:05:08.849 --> 00:05:17.479
even though we all know that it exists.

